  "response_text": "This is a great request. Living in a dorm with a mini-fridge, a microwave, and maybe a kettle or rice cooker is a common challenge. The key is to focus on **no-cook**, **microwave-only**, and **assembly** meals.\n\nHere is a complete **Weekly Meal & Fitness Plan** designed for a dorm setting. It assumes you have access to a communal kitchen maybe once a week for hard-boiled eggs (or you can buy them pre-made), but primarily relies on your room.\n\n### The \"Dorm Kitchen\" Essentials (Buy These)\n- **Tools:** Microwave-safe bowl, plate, mug, fork/spoon, cutting board (small), knife.\n- **Pantry Staples:** Oatmeal (instant or rolled), peanut butter, canned beans (black, chickpeas), canned tuna/salmon/chicken, whole-wheat tortillas, rice cakes, nuts, seeds, protein powder.\n- **Fridge Staples:** Greek yogurt, milk (dairy or plant-based), pre-cooked hard-boiled eggs, baby spinach, carrots, bell peppers, hummus, shredded cheese, pre-cooked chicken strips, frozen berries, frozen vegetables (broccoli, peas).\n\n---\n\n## The Weekly Meal Plan (Microwave & No-Cook)\n\n| Day | Breakfast (5 mins) | Lunch (5 mins, no-cook) | Dinner (10 mins, microwave) | Snacks (No prep) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Mon** | **Overnight Oats** (mix oats, milk, yogurt, berries in a jar the night before) | **Tuna Salad Wrap** (canned tuna + mayo + spinach in a tortilla) | **Microwave \"Burrito Bowl\"** (microwave rice pouch + canned black beans + salsa + shredded cheese + Greek yogurt) | Apple + peanut butter |\n| **Tue** | **Greek Yogurt Bowl** (yogurt + granola + sliced banana) | **Hummus & Veggie Plate** (baby carrots, bell pepper strips, cucumber with hummus + pita chips) | **Microwave Scrambled Eggs** (2 eggs whisked in a mug with milk, microwave 45 sec, stir, 30 sec) + pre-cooked chicken strips + frozen broccoli | Handful of almonds |\n| **Wed** | **Peanut Butter Rice Cakes** (2 rice cakes + PB + banana slices) | **Leftover Burrito Bowl** (reheat from Mon) | **\"Deconstructed\" Chicken Salad** (bagged salad mix + pre-cooked chicken strips + cherry tomatoes + shredded cheese + bottled dressing) | Cottage cheese + pepper |\n| **Thu** | **Oatmeal in a Mug** (instant oats + water/milk + frozen berries, microwave 2 mins) | **Tuna & Crackers** (canned tuna + whole-wheat crackers + apple slices) | **Microwave \"Pasta\"** (microwave pre-cooked pasta or ramen *without seasoning* + jarred pesto + frozen peas + canned chickpeas) | Protein shake |\n| **Fri** | **Same as Mon** (Overnight Oats) | **Leftover Chicken Salad** (from Wed) | **\"Dorm Nachos\"** (tortilla chips + canned chili beans + shredded cheese, microwave 1 min, top with salsa & Greek yogurt) | String cheese |\n| **Sat** | **Bagel with Cream Cheese** (store-bought bagel) + hard-boiled egg | **\"Snack Plate Lunch\"** (cheese cubes, salami/pepperoni, grapes, almonds, crackers) | **Microwave \"Stuffed Sweet Potato\"** (microwave a sweet potato 5-7 mins, split open, top with black beans, salsa, and Greek yogurt) | Popcorn (microwave bag) |\n| **Sun** | **Yogurt Parfait** (layered yogurt, granola, frozen berries) | **Leftover Sweet Potato** (from Sat) | **\"Clean-out-the-fridge\" Stir-fry** (microwave frozen mixed veggies + pre-cooked chicken + a splash of soy sauce + rice pouch) | Dark chocolate square |\n\n---\n\n## The Weekly Fitness Plan (No Gym Required)\n\nThis plan uses **bodyweight exercises** you can do in your dorm room or a nearby quiet hallway/yard. It takes **20-30 minutes** per session.\n\n**Warm-up (Every Day):** 2 mins of jumping jacks, high knees, arm circles.\n\n| Day | Workout Focus | Exercises (Do 3 rounds) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Mon** | **Full Body Strength** | 1. **Squats** (15 reps) <br> 2. **Push-ups** (on knees if needed, 10 reps) <br> 3. **Plank** (hold 30 sec) <br> 4. **Lunges** (10 each leg) |\n| **Tue** | **Cardio & Core** | 1. **High Knees** (30 sec) <br> 2. **Bicycle Crunches** (20 reps) <br> 3. **Burpees** (10 reps, no push-up if tired) <br> 4. **Mountain Climbers** (30 sec) |\n| **Wed** | **Active Recovery** | **20-30 min walk** outside (listen to a podcast or music). Stretch for 5 mins after. |\n| **Thu** | **Upper Body Focus** | 1. **Push-ups** (as many as possible) <br> 2. **Triceps Dips** (use the edge of your bed or a sturdy chair, 10 reps) <br> 3. **Plank with Shoulder Taps** (alternate touching opposite shoulder, 10 each side) <br> 4. **Superman Holds** (lie on stomach, lift arms & legs, hold 15 sec) |\n| **Fri** | **Lower Body Focus** | 1. **Goblet Squats** (hold a water bottle or textbook, 15 reps) <br> 2. **Reverse Lunges** (10 each leg) <br> 3. **Glute Bridges** (lie on back, lift hips, 15 reps) <br> 4. **Calf Raises** (20 reps) |\n| **Sat** | **Fun Cardio** | **20 mins of your choice:** Jump rope (if you have one), dance to a workout video on YouTube, or go for a run/bike ride. |\n| **Sun** | **Rest & Stretch** | Full body stretching (neck, shoulders, hamstrings, quads, back). Foam roll if you have one. |\n\n---\n\n## Crucial Tips for Dorm Success\n\n1.  **Hydration:** Keep a large water bottle on your desk. Drink it all. Avoid sugary drinks.\n2.  **Protein is Key:** Since cooking meat is hard, rely on **Greek yogurt, cottage",
